Patient: What kind of food should I eat?

Healthcare Educator: Aim for foods low in sodium and fats. Include more fruits, vegetables, and lean proteins.

Patient: But I love traditional foods. How can I change that?

Healthcare Educator: You can still enjoy them, but modify the recipes. Use less salt and healthier oils.

Patient: Where can I get fresh food? My neighborhood isn't safe.

Healthcare Educator: Consider online grocery deliveries, or farmers markets if possible. They can provide fresh food options.

Patient: This sounds difficult. How can I make these changes?

Healthcare Educator: A dietitian can help. They can provide guidelines on incorporating healthy foods into your meals. 

Patient: What will happen if I don't change my diet?

Healthcare Educator: Unhealthy diet can worsen your heart failure. Healthy food can help manage it better.